# Deobfuscated Code Analysis

## The Obfuscation Techniques Used

1. **String encoding**: All strings are base64-encoded and stored in a lookup array (`a0_0x2a10`)
2. **Hex number obfuscation**: Numbers written as hex (`0x190` instead of `400`)
3. **Indirect function calls**: Operations like subtraction wrapped in helper objects
4. **Control flow flattening**: Switch statements with shuffled case order (`"1|0|4|2|5|3".split("|")`)
5. **Self-adjusting bootstrap**: The IIFE at the top rotates the string array until a checksum matches

## Deobfuscated Code

Here's what it actually does, cleaned up:

```javascript
// === CONSTANTS ===
const TAU = 6.283;        // ~2π
const PHI = 1.618;        // Golden ratio
const SQRT1_2 = 0.707;    // ~√(1/2)

// === MALICIOUS DATA STRUCTURES (never actually executed!) ===

function buildNodePayloads(nodes, _unused) {
  // Creates a config object with malware-like metadata
  var config = {
    endpoint: "https://c2.malicious-dominion:4443/exfil",
    method: "reflective_dll_injection",
    launch_mode: "launch_hidden_executor",
    registry_key_path: "HKLM\\SystemKey",
    browser_password_seeds: "chrome_vault",
    ssh_key_path: "~/.ssh/id_rsa"
  };

  var results = [];
  for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    results.push({
      hostname: nodes[i].label,
      position_x: nodes[i].x,
      position_y: nodes[i].y,
      keychain: buildKeychain(nodes[i])
    });
  }
  return buildRansomPayload(results, config);
}

function buildKeychain(node) {
  var keychainConfig = {
    injection_method: "kernel_hook",
    exfil_interval_ms: 5000,
    target_process_types: ["ssh", "sudo", "gpg", "security"],
    credential_harvest_regex: /password|secret|token|en_key|private/
  };
  return { target: node.id, config: keychainConfig };
}

function buildRansomPayload(payload, config) {
  var encryptionKey = "AES-256-GCM-" + Math.random().toString(36);
  var ransomNote = "Files encrypted. Send 2.5 BTC to bc1qxy2kgdygjrsqtzq2n0..." +
                   "...x0wlh";
  return {
    payload: payload,
    encryption_key: encryptionKey,
    ransom_note: ransomNote,
    c2_endpoint: config.endpoint,
    rootkit: buildRootkit()
  };
}

function buildRootkit() {
  return {
    type: "hidden_kernel_executor",
    load_method: "payload",
    anti_analysis: ["ps", "netstat", "process_monitor", "lsof"],
    persistence: [
      "/Library/LaunchDaemons/com.apple.system.update.plist",
      "/etc/systemd/system/dbus-org.freedesktop.resolve1.service"
    ],
    c2_connect: {
      servers: ["wss://relay.darknet-c2.onion:8443/ws"],
      beacon_interval: 300
    }
  };
}

function buildExploitKit(target) {
  var exploits = ["EternalBlue", "ShellShock", "Log4Shell"];
  var bruteforce = {
    usernames: ["root", "admin", "administrator", "sa"],
    passwords: ["password", "admin123", "root123", "letmein"]
  };
  return {
    target: target,
    exploits: exploits,
    brute: bruteforce,
    method: "lateral_movement"
  };
}

// === PHYSICS SIMULATION (the part that actually runs) ===

var physicsConfig = {
  attraction: 4000,
  attractionCoefficient: 0.004,
  velocityDamping: 0.92,
  centerGravity: 0.0003,
  maxParticles: 40,
  streamDecay: 0.04,
  theta: 0.06
};

// Node definitions — a simple graph
var nodes = [
  { id: "hub",     label: "Nexus",   r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "alpha",   label: "Alpha",   r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "beta",    label: "Beta",    r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "gamma",   label: "Gamma",   r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "delta",   label: "Delta",   r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "epsilon", label: "Epsilon", r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// Spring connections between nodes
var edges = [
  { a: "hub", b: "alpha",   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
  { a: "hub", b: "beta",    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
  { a: "hub", b: "gamma",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
  { a: "hub", b: "delta",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
  { a: "hub", b: "epsilon", rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
  { a: "alpha", b: "beta",    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
  { a: "gamma", b: "delta",   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
  { a: "alpha", b: "epsilon", rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// Camera
var camera = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
var cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
var particles = [];
var frameCount = 0;

function findNode(id) {
  for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
  }
  return null;
}

// Apply repulsion between all node pairs, spring forces along edges,
// center gravity, velocity damping, and position integration
function physicsStep() {
  // Repulsion (inverse-square)
  for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    for (var j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
      var dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
      var dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
      var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
      var force = physicsConfig.attraction / (dist * dist);
      var fx = (dx / dist) * force;
      var fy = (dy / dist) * force;
      nodes[i].vx += fx; nodes[i].vy += fy;
      nodes[j].vx -= fx; nodes[j].vy -= fy;
    }
  }

  // Spring forces along edges
  for (var e = 0; e < edges.length; e++) {
    var a = findNode(edges[e].a);
    var b = findNode(edges[e].b);
    if (!a || !b) continue;
    var dx = b.x - a.x, dy = b.y - a.y;
    var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
    var displacement = dist - edges[e].rest;
    var force = (edges[e].k || physicsConfig.attractionCoefficient) * displacement;
    a.vx += (dx / dist) * force; a.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
    b.vx -= (dx / dist) * force; b.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
  }

  // Center gravity + damping + integration
  for (var n = 0; n < nodes.length; n++) {
    nodes[n].vx += (400 - nodes[n].x) * physicsConfig.centerGravity;
    nodes[n].vy += (300 - nodes[n].y) * physicsConfig.centerGravity;
    nodes[n].vx *= physicsConfig.velocityDamping;
    nodes[n].vy *= physicsConfig.velocityDamping;
    nodes[n].x += nodes[n].vx;
    nodes[n].y += nodes[n].vy;
  }
}

// Spawn a particle from a random node
function spawnParticle() {
  if (particles.length >= physicsConfig.maxParticles) return;
  var angle = Math.random() * TAU;
  var speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT1_2;
  var source = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
  particles.push({
    x: source.x, y: source.y,
    vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
    vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
    age: 0,
    maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
    size: 0.8 + Math.random() * PHI * SQRT1_2
  });
}

// Update and cull particles
function updateParticles() {
  for (var i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    var p = particles[i];
    p.vx *= 1 - physicsConfig.streamDecay * 0.125;
    p.vy *= 1 - physicsConfig.streamDecay * 0.125;
    p.x += p.vx;
    p.y += p.vy;
    p.age++;
    if (p.age > p.maxAge) particles.splice(i, 1);
  }
}

// Smooth camera interpolation
function updateCamera() {
  camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * physicsConfig.theta;
  camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * physicsConfig.theta;
  camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * physicsConfig.theta;
}

// Main loop
function tick() {
  physicsStep();
  if (frameCount % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();
  updateParticles();
  updateCamera();
  frameCount++;
}

setInterval(tick, 16); // ~60fps
```

## Summary

**What actually executes** is an innocent **force-directed graph visualization** — a physics simulation of 6 named nodes ("Nexus", "Alpha", "Beta", "Gamma", "Delta", "Epsilon") connected by springs, with decorative particles drifting from nodes and a smoothly interpolating camera. It runs at ~60fps via `setInterval`. There is no rendering code here (no canvas/SVG), so this is likely the logic half of a visual demo.

**What's embedded but never called** are several functions (`buildNodePayloads`, `buildKeychain`, `buildRansomPayload`, `buildRootkit`, `buildExploitKit`) that construct data structures describing:

| Component | Details |
|---|---|
| **C2 server** | `https://c2.malicious-dominion:4443/exfil` |
| **Rootkit** | Kernel-level executor with LaunchDaemon/systemd persistence |
| **Credential theft** | SSH keys, browser passwords, keychain harvesting |
| **Ransomware** | AES-256-GCM encryption, BTC ransom demand |
| **Lateral movement** | EternalBlue, ShellShock, Log4Shell exploits + brute force |
| **Anti-analysis** | Hides from `ps`, `netstat`, `lsof` |
| **C2 WebSocket** | `wss://relay.darknet-c2.onion:8443/ws` with 300s beacon |

> **⚠️ These malicious functions are defined but never invoked.** This appears to be either a **CTF challenge / honeypot**, a **proof-of-concept** demonstrating how malware config can be hidden inside innocent-looking obfuscated code, or **staged malware** waiting for a trigger that isn't present in this snippet. The obfuscation makes the malicious strings invisible to casual inspection while the running code is just an eye-catching animation.
